<https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/pension-protection-fund> <http://ogp.me/ns#description> "The Pension Protection Fund (PPF) pays compensation to members of eligible defined benefit pension schemes, when there is a qualifying insolvency event in relation to the employer and where there are insufficient assets in the pension scheme to cover Pension Protection Fund levels of compensation. PPF is a public corporation of the Department for Work and Pensions ."@en .
